1
00:00:56,090 --> 00:00:58,968
FILING FOR LOVE

2
00:01:03,264 --> 00:01:06,058
2013 YEONHYANG TEMPLE CUISINE RETREAT
NOV. 15 TO 22, 2013

3
00:01:30,916 --> 00:01:33,711
MOTHER JOO KYUNG-HEE,
REMEMBERED BY JOO IN-A

4
00:01:38,465 --> 00:01:41,176
Mom's resting place
has such crisp air.

5
00:02:00,821 --> 00:02:04,491
Mister, untie me!
Let me go right now!

6
00:02:04,533 --> 00:02:05,826
What are you doing to me?

7
00:02:05,909 --> 00:02:07,870
Mister, let me go!

8
00:02:07,953 --> 00:02:09,079
I have to get out of here!

9
00:02:09,163 --> 00:02:11,040
- I have to leave!
- Mom!

10
00:02:11,165 --> 00:02:12,541
- I have to get out!
- Mom!

11
00:02:12,625 --> 00:02:15,085
Untie me right now!

12
00:02:15,336 --> 00:02:17,671
What are you doing? No! Don't!

13
00:02:17,713 --> 00:02:21,508
- Hold on to her tight.
- No! Let me go!

14
00:02:22,343 --> 00:02:23,802
- Grab her tightly!
- No!

15
00:02:28,891 --> 00:02:30,934
Jumping from there
will cause too much trouble.

16
00:02:33,937 --> 00:02:35,522
You'll land smack on a hiking trail.

17
00:02:36,565 --> 00:02:39,193
It must've been a long walk up here.

18
00:02:40,235 --> 00:02:42,905
Why don't you put that will
and energy toward trying to live?

19
00:02:44,281 --> 00:02:45,574
Enjoy the clean air and go home.

20
00:02:45,658 --> 00:02:47,326
The walk down is much nicer.

21
00:03:06,053 --> 00:03:08,472
I think you missed the last bus.

22
00:03:10,015 --> 00:03:12,142
Are there really no more buses today?

23
00:03:12,726 --> 00:03:13,811
Where are you headed?

24
00:03:14,687 --> 00:03:16,313
- I'll drop you off.
- I'm too afraid

25
00:03:16,397 --> 00:03:18,816
to accept a ride from someone
who just tried to end his life.

26
00:03:19,358 --> 00:03:20,442
No, thank you.

27
00:03:22,236 --> 00:03:23,529
You have a point.

28
00:03:26,407 --> 00:03:27,366
Excuse me.

29
00:03:28,617 --> 00:03:29,993
I hope to see you again alive.

30
00:03:47,386 --> 00:03:48,470
Hello.

31
00:03:48,554 --> 00:03:51,140
I'm Lee Tae-kwon, the new recruit.

32
00:03:51,265 --> 00:03:52,266
I hope we all get along.

33
00:03:54,518 --> 00:03:56,645
There's one last person to introduce.

34
00:03:56,729 --> 00:04:00,357
Joo In-a beat her competition
for first place

35
00:04:00,441 --> 00:04:02,234
among her batch of new recruits.

36
00:04:02,359 --> 00:04:03,610
She's a true elite.

37
00:04:03,819 --> 00:04:06,321
I'll show what a first-place recruit
can do. Thank you.

38
00:04:06,989 --> 00:04:08,115
I hope we work well together.

39
00:04:13,412 --> 00:04:14,538
Cheers.

40
00:04:15,497 --> 00:04:16,540
Good job.

41
00:04:25,966 --> 00:04:28,677
Why is this group so silent?

42
00:04:30,721 --> 00:04:34,266
Ms. Joo, pour Mr. Jeon a drink.

43
00:04:34,391 --> 00:04:35,392
Oh, sure.

44
00:05:01,460 --> 00:05:03,712
So I heard you're the son
of Haemu Group's president.

45
00:05:04,171 --> 00:05:05,923
A third-generation chaebol heir
I’d only heard about.

46
00:05:09,259 --> 00:05:12,179
Then you must know
I'm not valued much as a son.

47
00:05:15,641 --> 00:05:17,309
Was that why you were struggling

48
00:05:17,434 --> 00:05:18,852
when we crossed paths back then?

49
00:05:21,939 --> 00:05:23,315
I hope we work well together

50
00:05:23,565 --> 00:05:24,608
Manager Jeon Jae-yeol.

51
00:05:33,075 --> 00:05:34,493
I really hoped to see you again.

52
00:05:37,037 --> 00:05:38,163
I'm glad I chose to live.

53
00:05:49,883 --> 00:05:51,176
What do you mean?

54
00:05:51,802 --> 00:05:55,097
Mr. Jeon headed this project
from the initial planning stage.

55
00:05:55,180 --> 00:05:56,765
It just need to be signed
to be approved

56
00:05:56,849 --> 00:05:58,141
and you want me
to omit Mr. Jeon's name?

57
00:05:58,225 --> 00:06:01,311
Ms. Joo, you need to see
the big picture here.

58
00:06:01,812 --> 00:06:03,438
Don't you see his stepbrother

59
00:06:03,522 --> 00:06:05,816
has been taking all the credit
since he joined the company?

60
00:06:06,984 --> 00:06:09,152
So what? Are you saying that's okay?

61
00:06:10,779 --> 00:06:13,365
- If the president were to hear...
- Oh, come on.

62
00:06:13,574 --> 00:06:16,743
All this is possible
because the president is allowing it.

63
00:06:19,371 --> 00:06:20,539
You've heard, haven't you?

64
00:06:21,081 --> 00:06:22,332
About Mr. Jeon's birth mother.

65
00:06:22,666 --> 00:06:24,334
He won't ever make it.

66
00:06:24,418 --> 00:06:26,920
We must side
with his younger brother.

67
00:06:27,671 --> 00:06:30,215
Fly to Dubai and close the deal.
There's a flight in two hours.

68
00:06:30,340 --> 00:06:32,009
- You need to hurry.
- In-a.

69
00:06:33,260 --> 00:06:35,012
This will only get you in trouble.

70
00:06:36,096 --> 00:06:38,974
This isn't even my project.

71
00:06:39,474 --> 00:06:40,517
It's the company's.

72
00:06:42,811 --> 00:06:44,313
Still, it's too unfair and wrong.

73
00:06:44,396 --> 00:06:46,189
You did all the hard work.

74
00:06:47,858 --> 00:06:49,067
It's enough for me
that you know that.

75
00:06:57,284 --> 00:07:00,996
Everyone's too cruel.
They're so mean and nasty.

76
00:07:02,039 --> 00:07:03,123
In-a.

77
00:07:06,960 --> 00:07:07,961
I swear

78
00:07:09,713 --> 00:07:11,798
I'll protect you
for as long as I'm here.

79
00:07:12,633 --> 00:07:14,551
Whatever happens,
even if the sky falls...

80
00:07:17,554 --> 00:07:19,222
I'll be on your side, Jae-yeol.

81
00:07:25,604 --> 00:07:27,397
This is so darn infuriating.

82
00:07:41,244 --> 00:07:42,287
So you were a couple.

83
00:07:45,123 --> 00:07:46,667
We were once a couple.

84
00:07:50,379 --> 00:07:51,380
Why did you break up?

85
00:07:53,298 --> 00:07:54,341
Just because

86
00:07:55,092 --> 00:07:58,095
he found someone
within his league to marry

87
00:07:58,720 --> 00:08:00,097
and I wanted to live
a life of my own.

88
00:08:01,098 --> 00:08:02,432
It's one of those boring
and obvious reasons.

89
00:08:03,141 --> 00:08:04,226
It's all in the past.

90
00:08:05,811 --> 00:08:06,812
Are you sure of that?

91
00:08:08,730 --> 00:08:09,731
What does that mean?

92
00:08:18,198 --> 00:08:19,366
There was a tip-off

93
00:08:20,200 --> 00:08:22,869
claiming you were having
an inappropriate workplace affair.

94
00:08:23,745 --> 00:08:26,289
That's you and the VP, isn't it?

95
00:08:54,568 --> 00:08:55,569
You came back.

96
00:08:55,819 --> 00:08:58,613
It has been a long time,
Vice President Jeon.

97
00:09:03,660 --> 00:09:04,870
I missed you.

98
00:09:09,082 --> 00:09:10,959
I think it was the day
I returned to the head office.

99
00:09:12,586 --> 00:09:14,713
He was just pleased to see me again.
It didn't mean anything else.

100
00:09:18,050 --> 00:09:19,384
It didn't mean anything?

101
00:09:20,677 --> 00:09:22,054
The situation I just witnessed

102
00:09:23,680 --> 00:09:25,015
would signify otherwise.

103
00:09:27,100 --> 00:09:29,728
Is this the vice president's
one-sided feeling?

104
00:09:30,979 --> 00:09:31,980
Or is there

105
00:09:33,315 --> 00:09:35,025
something left between you two?

106
00:10:02,636 --> 00:10:04,805
I don't want you to come here
whenever you please.

107
00:10:07,933 --> 00:10:09,643
- In-a.
- Take your hands off me.

108
00:10:11,019 --> 00:10:12,062
Let go.

109
00:10:18,568 --> 00:10:20,195
The VP and I...

110
00:10:21,488 --> 00:10:23,198
He's an executive,
and I'm just his subordinate.

111
00:10:23,698 --> 00:10:25,117
That's all it is.

112
00:10:25,659 --> 00:10:27,285
I have no residual feelings
toward him.

113
00:10:34,751 --> 00:10:36,628
To be honest, I suspected you
after I got the tip-off.

114
00:10:37,504 --> 00:10:39,923
So I investigated about you
and tailed you.

115
00:10:40,590 --> 00:10:42,300
I even followed you home
for a stakeout.

116
00:10:45,929 --> 00:10:46,930
I knew it.

117
00:10:47,472 --> 00:10:48,723
There's a reason you're the ace.

118
00:10:48,932 --> 00:10:51,852
I never imagined
the guy would turn out to be the VP.

119
00:10:53,854 --> 00:10:54,855
So, what now?

120
00:10:56,690 --> 00:10:59,192
What's your conclusion
as the handler of PM cases?

121
00:11:09,411 --> 00:11:10,453
I don't know.

122
00:11:12,664 --> 00:11:13,915
I want to believe

123
00:11:15,458 --> 00:11:17,127
everything you say at face value

124
00:11:18,837 --> 00:11:20,213
that it's all in the past

125
00:11:20,630 --> 00:11:23,008
and however the VP feels about you

126
00:11:23,884 --> 00:11:25,427
you feel nothing for him now.

127
00:11:26,511 --> 00:11:27,512
But...

128
00:11:29,222 --> 00:11:31,600
I think it's my heart
that wants to believe that.

129
00:11:38,148 --> 00:11:39,482
Give me some time.

130
00:11:40,692 --> 00:11:42,277
I'll think about it
as cool-headed as possible.

131
00:12:29,741 --> 00:12:33,161
EPISODE 7:
TO HER LOVER

132
00:12:37,207 --> 00:12:39,376
- Five packs of soju cups.
- Five packs of soju cups.

133
00:12:39,501 --> 00:12:42,254
- And five packs of paper cups.
- Five of those.

134
00:12:42,379 --> 00:12:44,839
- Two packs of plastic spoons.
- Oh, and seltzer water.

135
00:12:44,923 --> 00:12:45,924
- Seltzer water?
- Yes.

136
00:12:46,007 --> 00:12:47,509
- We didn't order any.
- For highballs.

137
00:12:47,592 --> 00:12:49,886
Okay, add seltzer to the list.

138
00:12:50,220 --> 00:12:51,972
And then...

139
00:12:52,055 --> 00:12:54,599
Mr. Moo, can you stay still?

140
00:12:54,683 --> 00:12:56,226
I'm finding it hard to focus already.

141
00:12:56,309 --> 00:12:58,979
I guess I'm excited. We haven't
held any workshop in a while.

142
00:12:59,562 --> 00:13:01,147
I did some thinking, you see.

143
00:13:01,356 --> 00:13:04,651
No workshop is complete
without a barbecue.

144
00:13:04,734 --> 00:13:06,027
It wouldn't feel right.

145
00:13:06,319 --> 00:13:07,612
Don't you think, White Blood Cell?

146
00:13:07,696 --> 00:13:09,030
You're right. It wouldn't feel right.

147
00:13:09,114 --> 00:13:10,782
- Right?
- Hae-young.

148
00:13:10,907 --> 00:13:13,952
Eleven people will drive there,
and the rest will take the bus.

149
00:13:14,077 --> 00:13:15,203
Okay.

150
00:13:15,287 --> 00:13:16,496
Send a list of names

151
00:13:16,579 --> 00:13:18,498
- to the bus driver.
- Okay.

152
00:13:19,249 --> 00:13:22,502
When did you two
get close enough to speak casually?

153
00:13:22,585 --> 00:13:23,920
You caught on real slow.

154
00:13:24,421 --> 00:13:26,589
Mr. Cha, did you finish
your tasks for the day?

155
00:13:26,673 --> 00:13:27,882
Why are you over here?

156
00:13:27,966 --> 00:13:30,135
Did you text the whole office?

157
00:13:30,260 --> 00:13:32,804
I will right now.
Gosh, I'm sick of your nagging.

158
00:13:33,596 --> 00:13:37,017
Hae-young. We should order
pork belly and pork neck.

159
00:13:37,100 --> 00:13:38,310
Okay, fine.

160
00:13:38,435 --> 00:13:39,602
- Will you order some?
- Yes.

161
00:13:39,686 --> 00:13:42,314
- Yes, buy some pork. A big chunk.
- Just pork neck.

162
00:14:07,672 --> 00:14:09,924
Assistant Manager Noh Ki-jun, is it?

163
00:14:11,134 --> 00:14:12,177
Can he be trusted?

164
00:14:12,886 --> 00:14:14,137
He's an arrogant punk.

165
00:14:16,806 --> 00:14:19,059
He's definitely not
the submissive type.

166
00:14:21,144 --> 00:14:22,479
What did he mean?

167
00:14:22,896 --> 00:14:24,439
That something that can't work
still can work.

168
00:14:24,939 --> 00:14:26,358
What cannot work

169
00:14:27,275 --> 00:14:28,610
and what can work?

170
00:14:31,029 --> 00:14:32,989
You're Haemu Group's vice president.

171
00:14:33,531 --> 00:14:35,200
Why would you mind a lowly employee?

172
00:14:35,784 --> 00:14:37,285
You must have
other important matters.

173
00:15:01,017 --> 00:15:02,018
Ms. Joo.

174
00:15:02,602 --> 00:15:05,271
- Yes, Hae-young.
- Haemu issued new credit cards.

175
00:15:05,355 --> 00:15:06,856
Give me your old one. I'll cut it up.

176
00:15:07,273 --> 00:15:09,526
- It's in my bag. I'll get it.
- Okay, thank you.

177
00:15:25,458 --> 00:15:26,501
See?

178
00:15:27,836 --> 00:15:28,878
Something that can't work

179
00:15:30,422 --> 00:15:31,714
still can work.

180
00:15:53,486 --> 00:15:56,239
Does that issue have to wait
until the next meeting?

181
00:15:56,448 --> 00:15:58,074
It is a bit too early to bring up

182
00:15:58,199 --> 00:16:00,910
although what you want
is what matters most.

183
00:16:02,996 --> 00:16:05,915
You met with Director Han, right?

184
00:16:05,999 --> 00:16:07,083
Yes, I did.

185
00:16:18,595 --> 00:16:19,637
Noh Ki-jun.

186
00:16:20,346 --> 00:16:21,723
Will you knock first?

187
00:16:23,141 --> 00:16:24,601
I'm cooking ramyeon.
Do you want some?

188
00:16:24,934 --> 00:16:26,060
No.

189
00:16:26,436 --> 00:16:28,938
- Don't you dare ask for a bite.
- Hey, A-jeong.

190
00:16:31,316 --> 00:16:33,985
What's your VP like?

191
00:16:36,696 --> 00:16:39,991
Why do you say "your VP"?
He's yours, too.

192
00:16:42,285 --> 00:16:43,286
You're right.

193
00:16:44,245 --> 00:16:45,413
He's my boss, too.

194
00:16:45,622 --> 00:16:47,248
Why are you
suddenly asking about him?

195
00:16:47,707 --> 00:16:50,960
I thought you were
trying to figure out Joo In-a.

196
00:16:52,170 --> 00:16:55,340
You rushed out saying
you wanted to figure out

197
00:16:55,423 --> 00:16:56,633
your relationship with her.

198
00:16:58,134 --> 00:16:59,177
Did you figure it out?

199
00:16:59,302 --> 00:17:01,137
I figured out one thing for sure.

200
00:17:02,555 --> 00:17:03,890
That she's a darn tough woman.

201
00:17:05,016 --> 00:17:07,352
- What does that mean?
- I don't know. Forget it.

202
00:17:07,810 --> 00:17:09,062
Enjoy your ramyeon.

203
00:17:12,106 --> 00:17:13,149
What the heck?

204
00:17:35,004 --> 00:17:36,256
HAEMU GROUP

205
00:17:36,339 --> 00:17:39,384
2025 HAEMU GROUP
STRATEGIC PLANNING JOINT WORKSHOP

206
00:17:39,467 --> 00:17:41,803
HAEMU TRAINING CENTER

207
00:17:48,268 --> 00:17:50,144
- Oh, dear.
- My goodness.

208
00:17:53,856 --> 00:17:56,025
Gosh. Are we doing a barbecue?

209
00:17:56,150 --> 00:17:59,404
Of course, Ms. Joo.
A barbecue is a must at a workshop.

210
00:17:59,487 --> 00:18:01,698
I like the way you think, Mr. Moo.

211
00:18:02,657 --> 00:18:04,075
- I'll help with the stuff.
- What?

212
00:18:04,617 --> 00:18:05,868
- No!
- Don't!

213
00:18:05,952 --> 00:18:08,496
Let me pretend to be
an easygoing boss.

214
00:18:08,580 --> 00:18:09,706
- But...
- Oh, gosh...

215
00:18:10,123 --> 00:18:13,251
That must weigh at least 20kg.
She's pretty strong.

216
00:18:13,376 --> 00:18:15,587
- Move the boxes now.
- Yes, sir.

217
00:18:24,887 --> 00:18:26,764
You have a clinical condition
of acting tough.

218
00:18:29,434 --> 00:18:31,185
STRATEGIC PLANNING JOINT WORKSHOP

219
00:18:35,732 --> 00:18:37,942
A TIME TO CONNECT TO GROW

220
00:18:38,026 --> 00:18:39,068
The Planning Team.

221
00:18:39,819 --> 00:18:40,862
Human Resources.

222
00:18:41,779 --> 00:18:43,072
And the Audit Team.

223
00:18:45,033 --> 00:18:47,619
I just said your team names,
and I'm shuddering in fear.

224
00:18:50,622 --> 00:18:53,583
You work so hard
to keep our company going.

225
00:18:54,125 --> 00:18:55,627
At this workshop

226
00:18:56,169 --> 00:18:58,296
I hope you can forget
your strenuous workplace

227
00:18:58,421 --> 00:19:00,048
and relax and have a good time.

228
00:19:13,645 --> 00:19:15,938
Hang on. Why aren't you in bed?

229
00:19:16,189 --> 00:19:18,316
Isn't it almost midnight
where you are?

230
00:19:18,441 --> 00:19:20,818
I'm exhausted. Mom nags too much.

231
00:19:20,943 --> 00:19:23,196
Can't you just do as she says?

232
00:19:23,279 --> 00:19:25,657
She said she's been having headaches.

233
00:19:25,948 --> 00:19:26,991
Okay?

234
00:19:27,075 --> 00:19:29,118
Sleep well.
I'll talk to you tomorrow.

235
00:19:32,622 --> 00:19:35,958
Mr. Ahn, you should
take time off work soon

236
00:19:36,042 --> 00:19:37,877
to fly to the US to see your family.

237
00:19:38,169 --> 00:19:39,837
I didn't know you were watching.

238
00:19:40,463 --> 00:19:41,464
It's a pleasing sight.

239
00:19:42,090 --> 00:19:44,050
Are the others getting ready
for the next program?

240
00:19:44,133 --> 00:19:47,261
Oh, we'd initially planned
a team-building exercise

241
00:19:47,345 --> 00:19:48,680
but the two team heads said

242
00:19:48,805 --> 00:19:51,224
playing a sport is the best way
to boost teamwork.

243
00:19:53,476 --> 00:19:56,646
2025 HAEMU
STRATEGIC PLANNING JOINT WORKSHOP

244
00:20:00,149 --> 00:20:01,984
Warm up well and properly
so you don't get injured.

245
00:20:07,073 --> 00:20:09,701
Can't we watch an educational video
instead of playing futsal?

246
00:20:10,660 --> 00:20:12,328
Haven't you heard, Ms. Yoon?

247
00:20:13,121 --> 00:20:16,332
Ms. Joo said the MVP of today's match
can take the day off tomorrow.

248
00:20:22,463 --> 00:20:23,798
What are you doing?

249
00:20:26,134 --> 00:20:28,511
My gosh. What's gotten into you now?

250
00:20:30,138 --> 00:20:31,723
Why are you suddenly so eager now?

251
00:20:33,766 --> 00:20:35,601
- Faster!
- Goodness.

252
00:20:35,685 --> 00:20:37,019
I see you don't exercise much.

253
00:20:38,688 --> 00:20:39,772
Okay, everyone.

254
00:20:40,356 --> 00:20:41,941
Both men and women will play

255
00:20:42,024 --> 00:20:44,026
- so be sure no one gets hurt, okay?
- Yes, ma'am.

256
00:20:44,110 --> 00:20:46,571
Don't do anything
too aggressive like tackling.

257
00:20:46,696 --> 00:20:49,407
- Let's put safety first.
- Okay.

258
00:20:49,490 --> 00:20:51,451
We can't do that
if we're playing a competitive sport.

259
00:20:51,534 --> 00:20:52,910
It's all about winning.

260
00:20:52,994 --> 00:20:54,954
Take one of these beforehand.

261
00:20:55,204 --> 00:20:58,082
- Let's build some energy first.
- Thank you.

262
00:20:58,166 --> 00:20:59,417
- "Build energy"?
- Thank you.

263
00:20:59,500 --> 00:21:01,127
Energy is an asset, too, these days.

264
00:21:01,210 --> 00:21:04,464
We must save up when we can
to use when we must.

265
00:21:04,547 --> 00:21:07,133
- Thank you.
- At a moment like this.

266
00:21:10,261 --> 00:21:11,721
- Here.
- Thank you.

267
00:21:14,640 --> 00:21:15,892
Thank you.

268
00:21:23,065 --> 00:21:25,109
Wait, what's going on?

269
00:21:25,401 --> 00:21:26,903
Are you not going to share?

270
00:21:27,487 --> 00:21:30,531
Isn't this against the rules?
Isn't this a foul?

271
00:21:31,574 --> 00:21:32,742
Hello, sir!

272
00:21:32,992 --> 00:21:34,118
- Hello.
- Hello, sir.

273
00:21:34,243 --> 00:21:35,828
- Hello, sir.
- Hello.

274
00:21:36,287 --> 00:21:37,622
Mr. Jeon, sir.

275
00:21:37,955 --> 00:21:40,124
I thought you'd left
after the opening speech.

276
00:21:40,917 --> 00:21:43,669
I heard you'd planned something fun,
so I decided to come cheer you on.

277
00:21:43,753 --> 00:21:46,380
Will you be rooting
for the Audit Team?

278
00:21:46,464 --> 00:21:47,673
Of course not.

279
00:21:48,174 --> 00:21:49,759
You'll be cheering for HR, right?

280
00:21:49,842 --> 00:21:52,678
Let's see. I'm thinking of supporting
whichever is the winning team.

281
00:21:55,807 --> 00:21:56,933
That'll be our Audit Team.

282
00:21:58,226 --> 00:21:59,936
- That's no fun.
- What?

283
00:22:03,147 --> 00:22:05,316
Ignoring the process
and siding with the winner.

284
00:22:05,817 --> 00:22:06,818
Isn't that uncool?

285
00:22:11,823 --> 00:22:14,367
You speak as if you're the winner.

286
00:22:15,368 --> 00:22:16,410
Yes.

287
00:22:17,954 --> 00:22:19,247
Because I will win.

288
00:22:23,960 --> 00:22:27,588
Mr. Noh is excessively competitive.

289
00:22:28,840 --> 00:22:30,883
I don't think we can be teammates.

290
00:22:31,759 --> 00:22:33,094
How about we compete for real?

291
00:22:34,136 --> 00:22:36,389
Sir, are you really joining
the match?

292
00:22:36,806 --> 00:22:38,516
You have a meeting at 3 p.m.

293
00:22:38,891 --> 00:22:39,976
Cancel it.

294
00:23:06,127 --> 00:23:07,378
Kick it! Score a goal!

295
00:23:10,256 --> 00:23:11,257
What the...

296
00:23:12,508 --> 00:23:14,218
- Shoot.
- Stop! Stop it!

297
00:23:15,261 --> 00:23:16,554
- Ki-jun!
- Watch out!

298
00:23:17,263 --> 00:23:18,347
Kick it.

299
00:23:29,025 --> 00:23:30,902
Mr. Jeon! No!

300
00:23:31,027 --> 00:23:32,737
Mr. Jeon, are you all right?

301
00:23:32,820 --> 00:23:35,114
Are you okay, sir?
I told you to play nice!

302
00:23:35,197 --> 00:23:36,574
What should we do about you?

303
00:23:36,657 --> 00:23:39,410
What got into Mr. Noh?
Doesn't he know he should give in?

304
00:23:39,702 --> 00:23:42,246
Maybe he wants to be the MVP
to take tomorrow off.

305
00:23:42,330 --> 00:23:44,332
At this rate,
he might lose his job for good.

306
00:23:44,874 --> 00:23:46,250
It must be your leather shoes.

307
00:23:46,334 --> 00:23:47,585
- Wear my trainers.
- No, it's fine.

308
00:23:47,710 --> 00:23:50,630
No, please, sir. Wear mine.
That would be best for us all.

309
00:23:51,005 --> 00:23:53,507
- I'm fine.
- Mr. Noh is going too far.

310
00:24:15,404 --> 00:24:17,198
What the... Did you see that?
That was a foul!

311
00:24:17,281 --> 00:24:18,741
- Referee! Come on!
- Not a foul!

312
00:24:18,824 --> 00:24:20,576
- Get back up.
- It's not a foul.

313
00:24:20,660 --> 00:24:22,453
He didn't do anything wrong.
That was just a bump.

314
00:24:22,578 --> 00:24:23,579
Keep playing.

315
00:24:23,663 --> 00:24:24,789
That was uncalled for. It was...

316
00:24:24,914 --> 00:24:26,040
Sir, you can go ahead and score.

317
00:24:26,123 --> 00:24:28,751
- No, wait. Time out!
- What?

318
00:24:28,876 --> 00:24:31,003
Sir, go ahead. Score a goal.

319
00:24:31,087 --> 00:24:33,297
- What are you doing?
- Time out!

320
00:24:33,839 --> 00:24:35,424
You caught it all, didn't you?

321
00:24:35,508 --> 00:24:36,717
You filmed it, didn't you?

322
00:24:37,593 --> 00:24:39,428
Referee, VAR.
Let's watch the instant replay.

323
00:24:39,512 --> 00:24:41,639
- Boo.
- No, forget it.

324
00:24:41,722 --> 00:24:44,850
- Let's review the footage.
- You're being a nuisance!

325
00:24:44,934 --> 00:24:47,144
You're a nuisance.
That's uncool. Stop it.

326
00:25:05,162 --> 00:25:07,248
Let's keep things going!

327
00:25:07,331 --> 00:25:09,125
- Let's play!
- What the heck?

328
00:25:09,208 --> 00:25:10,835
Wait! That's not fair!

329
00:25:10,960 --> 00:25:12,420
Come on. Get the ball.

330
00:25:12,503 --> 00:25:13,671
- Bring it this way!
- No!

331
00:25:42,491 --> 00:25:43,576
Are you all right?

332
00:25:52,001 --> 00:25:53,669
You said you'd win at all costs.

333
00:25:55,129 --> 00:25:56,213
You must feel let down.

334
00:25:58,049 --> 00:25:59,925
Not exactly. It wasn't a fair match.

335
00:26:03,596 --> 00:26:06,348
Ms. Joo tripped you up on purpose.

336
00:26:06,849 --> 00:26:08,184
Let me apologize instead.

337
00:26:09,435 --> 00:26:11,187
In-a can be like that.

338
00:26:13,856 --> 00:26:15,232
What do you mean by "like that"?

339
00:26:16,567 --> 00:26:18,819
Oh, do you mean she has long legs?

340
00:26:20,988 --> 00:26:22,698
Do you have anyone like that?

341
00:26:23,783 --> 00:26:26,327
Someone who always takes your side
no matter what happens.

342
00:26:28,704 --> 00:26:30,706
Actually, we go way back.

343
00:26:36,670 --> 00:26:37,671
Sir.

344
00:26:38,964 --> 00:26:40,257
Are you hiding something?

345
00:26:42,051 --> 00:26:43,803
You speak too much as if to deflect.

346
00:26:44,720 --> 00:26:46,847
It looks like you're trying
to hide something from me.

347
00:27:05,366 --> 00:27:07,743
Mr. Choi got you a change of clothes.

348
00:27:08,410 --> 00:27:09,954
Shall I cancel
your evening plans, too?

349
00:27:12,915 --> 00:27:14,083
I live

350
00:27:15,126 --> 00:27:16,377
with a guy right now.

351
00:27:20,589 --> 00:27:21,590
Ms. Park.

352
00:27:23,425 --> 00:27:26,595
The nice guy you said you lived with.

353
00:27:28,305 --> 00:27:29,890
Is it Mr. Noh Ki-jun?

354
00:27:47,825 --> 00:27:48,826
What's with this?

355
00:27:50,578 --> 00:27:51,704
What the...

356
00:27:52,371 --> 00:27:54,123
Are you trying to smash the thing?

357
00:27:56,041 --> 00:27:57,168
Come and sit down.

358
00:28:03,048 --> 00:28:04,091
Take a seat.

359
00:28:10,848 --> 00:28:12,308
- Is it this foot?
- What the heck?

360
00:28:15,269 --> 00:28:16,437
It's this foot.

361
00:28:18,272 --> 00:28:19,815
- Let me see.
- No...

362
00:28:22,985 --> 00:28:25,196
It's not that swollen.

363
00:28:25,279 --> 00:28:26,488
Don't be silly.

364
00:28:26,947 --> 00:28:29,450
Look at this side.
My ankle is usually slim like this.

365
00:28:29,950 --> 00:28:31,327
What a crybaby.

366
00:28:33,704 --> 00:28:35,664
You hurt me
and now you're treating me?

367
00:28:36,957 --> 00:28:38,500
You tripped me up on purpose,
didn't you?

368
00:28:38,959 --> 00:28:40,878
How could you sabotage a teammate?

369
00:28:40,961 --> 00:28:44,215
Would the VP look bad
if he didn't get to score today?

370
00:28:44,506 --> 00:28:46,133
Why do you care so much about him?

371
00:28:46,550 --> 00:28:49,678
Your career at Haemu would've ended
if you'd gone any further.

372
00:28:50,429 --> 00:28:51,555
You should know
where to draw the line

373
00:28:51,639 --> 00:28:54,391
in front of your coworkers,
especially HR.

374
00:28:55,267 --> 00:28:56,852
Don't you know
they'd have avenged the VP

375
00:28:56,936 --> 00:28:58,562
even if the VP himself
didn't complain?

376
00:28:58,896 --> 00:29:00,022
Goodness.

377
00:29:00,856 --> 00:29:02,942
You've worked long enough
to know how things work.

378
00:29:03,859 --> 00:29:05,277
Why were you so childish out there?

379
00:29:10,741 --> 00:29:12,034
So that means you took my side

380
00:29:12,576 --> 00:29:13,661
and not the VP's.

381
00:29:15,246 --> 00:29:16,413
I'm not on anyone's side.

382
00:29:16,747 --> 00:29:20,209
I just did what a superior would do
to protect her subordinate.

383
00:29:30,552 --> 00:29:32,721
- Okay.
- What do you mean by "okay"?

384
00:29:32,805 --> 00:29:34,056
Your PM case.

385
00:29:34,890 --> 00:29:36,350
I think I can conclude it now.

386
00:29:37,059 --> 00:29:39,645
- Just like that?
- Other similar cases were closed

387
00:29:39,770 --> 00:29:41,897
without disciplinary action
when the subject denied the charges

388
00:29:42,398 --> 00:29:44,149
and no other definite proof
could be found.

389
00:29:45,734 --> 00:29:47,569
I couldn't decide

390
00:29:47,695 --> 00:29:50,948
whether I should investigate further
and drag the VP

391
00:29:51,365 --> 00:29:52,866
to the interview room to grill him.

392
00:29:55,411 --> 00:29:57,204
I realized something today.

393
00:29:59,415 --> 00:30:00,916
The way you both feel for each other

394
00:30:01,667 --> 00:30:02,793
is different.

395
00:30:08,507 --> 00:30:09,550
I believe you.

396
00:30:11,218 --> 00:30:12,303
I want to believe

397
00:30:14,888 --> 00:30:15,973
how you feel.

398
00:30:20,811 --> 00:30:21,895
How do you think

399
00:30:23,731 --> 00:30:24,773
I feel?

400
00:30:29,987 --> 00:30:30,988
What you did today...

401
00:30:31,947 --> 00:30:32,948
Was that really

402
00:30:33,782 --> 00:30:36,785
only just to protect
your subordinate?

403
00:30:44,543 --> 00:30:46,003
I showed you.

404
00:30:47,338 --> 00:30:48,464
Some things can work.

405
00:30:50,716 --> 00:30:52,301
I don't care how long it takes.

406
00:30:53,510 --> 00:30:55,471
Take a good look at your feelings.

407
00:30:58,265 --> 00:30:59,350
I'll wait.

408
00:31:19,119 --> 00:31:20,954
So Ms. Song, you were in the shower

409
00:31:21,288 --> 00:31:24,541
and it seemed like someone
filmed the shower booth, right?

410
00:31:24,625 --> 00:31:27,086
Yes, someone was clearly filming
with their cell phone.

411
00:31:28,379 --> 00:31:29,630
What did the culprit look like?

412
00:31:30,339 --> 00:31:31,465
Did you get a glimpse?

413
00:31:32,466 --> 00:31:34,843
I just got a glimpse
of the person's back

414
00:31:38,013 --> 00:31:40,849
and he was wearing
the men's T-shirt for our department.

415
00:31:44,311 --> 00:31:46,188
- So disgusting.
- That's crazy.

416
00:31:47,981 --> 00:31:49,316
An inside job.

417
00:31:50,943 --> 00:31:52,861
This is the lodging,
so there are no CCTVs around.

418
00:31:53,487 --> 00:31:54,822
Do you remember anything else?

419
00:31:55,697 --> 00:31:58,575
He must be using a white cell phone.

420
00:31:58,700 --> 00:32:01,578
What I saw was a white rectangle.

421
00:32:04,164 --> 00:32:05,207
Like a white cell phone?

422
00:32:05,290 --> 00:32:07,084
- I guess so.
- It's so gross.

423
00:32:07,209 --> 00:32:08,377
Everyone has that, right?

424
00:32:09,378 --> 00:32:10,462
This looks like

425
00:32:11,296 --> 00:32:13,006
a simple job to handle

426
00:32:14,842 --> 00:32:17,553
as long as
the male employees cooperate.

427
00:32:17,636 --> 00:32:19,138
And do what? Check their phones?

428
00:32:19,221 --> 00:32:22,891
Let's check only the white phones

429
00:32:23,058 --> 00:32:25,144
and he might have hidden
the phone he used to film with

430
00:32:25,727 --> 00:32:28,063
so we should check each room
for people's luggage.

431
00:32:31,400 --> 00:32:34,778
- You don't need to go that far...
- We need to check for sure.

432
00:32:37,072 --> 00:32:39,324
It may be an inconvenience,
but please cooperate.

433
00:32:39,408 --> 00:32:41,034
- Goodness.
- Goodness, no. We should do it.

434
00:32:41,660 --> 00:32:44,830
We cannot rule out the possibility
that the culprit is the Audit Team.

435
00:32:44,913 --> 00:32:47,583
To make it fair, let's have
one from Audit and one from HR

436
00:32:47,666 --> 00:32:49,835
conduct only the necessary amount
of verification.

437
00:32:49,918 --> 00:32:50,919
All right.

438
00:32:51,879 --> 00:32:54,298
Mr. Ahn, can you represent the HR?

439
00:32:54,590 --> 00:32:56,842
You're known to be upright and proper

440
00:32:56,925 --> 00:32:59,595
- so no one will complain.
- Yes, I understand.

441
00:33:17,779 --> 00:33:20,282
- Ms. Kim?
- Mr. Ahn, actually...

442
00:33:22,284 --> 00:33:23,327
You two look great together.

443
00:33:24,620 --> 00:33:26,747
- I didn't see anything.
- Yes, okay.

444
00:33:41,261 --> 00:33:42,804
Come on, Mr. Cha.

445
00:33:43,472 --> 00:33:45,974
You can't do this
as a member of the Audit Team.

446
00:33:55,150 --> 00:33:56,276
These were...

447
00:33:58,153 --> 00:33:59,696
These were from the barbecue.

448
00:34:04,326 --> 00:34:07,037
Never mind, Hyun-kyu.
Let's give the used ones to him.

449
00:34:07,454 --> 00:34:08,580
You can have these at home.

450
00:34:10,707 --> 00:34:11,792
Thanks.

451
00:34:22,678 --> 00:34:25,847
We searched through
the women's rooms just in case

452
00:34:25,931 --> 00:34:27,015
but couldn't find anything.

453
00:34:27,641 --> 00:34:29,476
We need to do everything we can.

454
00:34:32,521 --> 00:34:35,232
Are there no CCTVs near the entrance?

455
00:34:35,315 --> 00:34:38,735
Once the day breaks, I'll ask
the management and check right away.

456
00:34:39,069 --> 00:34:41,989
Anyway, you all worked hard
until this late.

457
00:34:42,072 --> 00:34:43,323
Let's go back and get some rest.

458
00:34:43,490 --> 00:34:45,367
All right. Great work.

459
00:34:50,038 --> 00:34:52,499
Mr. Ahn, you dropped this.

460
00:34:54,376 --> 00:34:55,836
- Oh.
- Huh?

461
00:34:56,086 --> 00:34:58,547
You smoke, Mr. Ahn? Since when?

462
00:35:00,424 --> 00:35:02,884
Once every now and then.
I smoke in secret.

463
00:35:03,594 --> 00:35:05,804
There's no need to smoke in secret
when you're at work.

464
00:35:06,430 --> 00:35:08,390
Do you want
to step out with me for a second?

465
00:35:08,682 --> 00:35:11,435
He must be using a white cell phone.

466
00:35:11,518 --> 00:35:13,520
No, I plan to quit very soon.

467
00:35:13,604 --> 00:35:14,896
Thanks, Mr. Noh. I'll have it.

468
00:35:15,606 --> 00:35:16,732
I don't want to give it back.

469
00:35:17,107 --> 00:35:18,483
- Why not?
- If you want to quit

470
00:35:18,567 --> 00:35:19,776
you should do it right away.

471
00:35:19,901 --> 00:35:21,069
Let me give you a hand.

472
00:35:21,153 --> 00:35:22,654
It's okay.
I'll quit starting tomorrow.

473
00:35:22,738 --> 00:35:25,616
No way. You need to make
these decisions right away.

474
00:35:25,741 --> 00:35:27,743
Mr. Noh, do not give it back.

475
00:35:28,076 --> 00:35:31,455
- No, ma'am.
- Gosh, you two are quite the tease.

476
00:35:31,538 --> 00:35:32,789
Give it back, Mr. Noh!

477
00:35:32,914 --> 00:35:36,126
Goodness, yes. Don't try to control
what someone else likes to do.

478
00:35:36,251 --> 00:35:38,045
And cigarettes
are quite expensive these days.

479
00:35:38,128 --> 00:35:39,129
Yes!

480
00:35:40,088 --> 00:35:41,381
This thing?

481
00:36:01,652 --> 00:36:03,362
What the...

482
00:36:04,696 --> 00:36:07,240
Why? What is it?

483
00:36:10,118 --> 00:36:12,287
Is this a camera?

484
00:36:15,582 --> 00:36:17,167
Mr. Ahn!

485
00:36:17,376 --> 00:36:18,794
I can't believe this!

486
00:36:22,506 --> 00:36:23,882
Have you lost your mind?

487
00:36:25,592 --> 00:36:27,052
Damn it.

488
00:36:34,267 --> 00:36:35,811
Look at all these.

489
00:36:37,479 --> 00:36:40,107
Looks like you didn’t care
the time or place when filming these.

490
00:36:40,357 --> 00:36:42,150
From the elevator ride to the office

491
00:36:42,275 --> 00:36:45,195
in-house cafeteria, restroom

492
00:36:45,278 --> 00:36:46,738
and the subway ride back home.

493
00:36:48,782 --> 00:36:49,783
Wait, how did you take this?

494
00:36:53,412 --> 00:36:54,496
No!

495
00:36:54,663 --> 00:36:57,249
Did you install cameras
under the staff members' desks?

496
00:36:58,333 --> 00:36:59,668
This is exactly that angle!

497
00:36:59,876 --> 00:37:01,962
Well, Ms. Joo, it's...

498
00:37:02,045 --> 00:37:03,213
How can you do this

499
00:37:03,338 --> 00:37:06,299
to your colleagues
whom you work with every single day?

500
00:37:06,550 --> 00:37:08,510
What do you take them for?

501
00:37:09,177 --> 00:37:10,971
All right. I get it.

502
00:37:12,389 --> 00:37:14,433
But I am fully cooperating, right?

503
00:37:14,808 --> 00:37:18,562
Blowing this up
won't do any good for the company.

504
00:37:18,645 --> 00:37:20,897
And it'll put our department
in a different position.

505
00:37:20,981 --> 00:37:23,191
- Think of our company's image, too.
- Sure, those are important.

506
00:37:23,650 --> 00:37:25,736
Our position and the company's image.

507
00:37:26,486 --> 00:37:27,571
That's why...

508
00:37:33,869 --> 00:37:35,579
we should blow this up
as much as we can.

509
00:37:35,996 --> 00:37:38,206
While other companies
are busy trying to cover up

510
00:37:38,415 --> 00:37:40,292
their in-house sexual assaults,
we'll be the company

511
00:37:40,375 --> 00:37:42,002
that punished
a spycam offender harshly

512
00:37:42,878 --> 00:37:44,296
to become a great example.

513
00:37:45,797 --> 00:37:46,798
Wait...

514
00:38:02,939 --> 00:38:03,982
Today

515
00:38:04,608 --> 00:38:06,860
I plan to eat at the cafeteria
for the first time in a while.

516
00:38:08,111 --> 00:38:10,197
Yes, sir. I'll call them right away.

517
00:38:10,614 --> 00:38:11,656
No.

518
00:38:12,699 --> 00:38:13,950
I'll go downstairs now.

519
00:38:19,206 --> 00:38:21,041
I don't like eating in the cafeteria.

520
00:38:21,124 --> 00:38:24,169
We have to eat so we can wrap up
Mr. Ahn's case and submit the report.

521
00:38:24,252 --> 00:38:25,420
Eat up.

522
00:38:25,545 --> 00:38:28,173
We have to eat something delicious
to work more efficiently

523
00:38:28,256 --> 00:38:29,633
and to put together a better report.

524
00:38:31,426 --> 00:38:32,677
But this is delicious.

525
00:38:33,261 --> 00:38:34,387
It's so good.

526
00:38:41,728 --> 00:38:42,771
What?

527
00:38:45,982 --> 00:38:47,108
May I join you?

528
00:38:48,693 --> 00:38:50,821
Sure, we didn't rent out the place.

529
00:38:51,112 --> 00:38:52,113
Have a seat.

530
00:39:06,127 --> 00:39:07,587
Jae-yeol is at the cafeteria?

531
00:39:07,796 --> 00:39:10,215
Yes, on top of that,
he sat with Ms. Joo

532
00:39:10,298 --> 00:39:12,717
and Mr. Noh Ki-jun
of Audit Team Three

533
00:39:12,801 --> 00:39:14,803
so it was a huge deal
in the Audit Team's office.

534
00:39:17,430 --> 00:39:19,808
My brother can be pretty sly, too.

535
00:39:20,725 --> 00:39:23,228
Well, I got to eat with Doo-gi,
the best

536
00:39:23,562 --> 00:39:24,729
of Audit Team One, didn't I?

537
00:39:26,523 --> 00:39:28,608
It's an honor, Mr. Jeon.

538
00:39:30,819 --> 00:39:32,112
How's work these days?

539
00:39:32,487 --> 00:39:34,698
Were you in charge
of our subsidiaries?

540
00:39:34,990 --> 00:39:37,325
Yes, I'm now in charge of the steels
and the pharmaceuticals.

541
00:39:40,579 --> 00:39:42,330
You're in charge
of the pharmaceuticals?

542
00:39:43,039 --> 00:39:44,916
If you're doing that now,
who used to be in charge?

543
00:39:47,252 --> 00:39:50,839
May I ask why you wish to know that?

544
00:39:51,423 --> 00:39:53,592
Well, it's not a big deal.

545
00:39:54,175 --> 00:39:56,344
Yesterday, I drank with people
from the pharmaceutical division.

546
00:39:56,636 --> 00:39:59,556
They said the Audit Team
used to pester them to death

547
00:39:59,681 --> 00:40:01,558
but not anymore these days.

548
00:40:02,517 --> 00:40:05,270
So I was wondering
if there was a power trip back then

549
00:40:05,353 --> 00:40:08,189
or if things
aren't working smoothly right now.

550
00:40:09,024 --> 00:40:10,358
But I guess
someone else was handling it.

551
00:40:11,109 --> 00:40:12,402
Yes, sir.

552
00:40:22,370 --> 00:40:23,914
I heard Mr. Noh played

553
00:40:24,915 --> 00:40:26,708
a big part
in the recent spycam incident.

554
00:40:27,125 --> 00:40:29,461
Yes, well, it's my job.

555
00:40:30,712 --> 00:40:33,381
He seems quite competent.
Why did you put him in charge of PM?

556
00:40:38,219 --> 00:40:39,346
I'm the type

557
00:40:39,804 --> 00:40:41,431
who's good at everything that I do.

558
00:40:46,978 --> 00:40:48,521
Gosh, so delicious.

559
00:41:20,804 --> 00:41:21,888
You two have

560
00:41:23,181 --> 00:41:24,766
a special relationship, don't you?

561
00:41:25,976 --> 00:41:28,353
Last time, I saw you two together
by chance

562
00:41:28,436 --> 00:41:30,939
while dropping Ms. Park off
at her place.

563
00:41:32,232 --> 00:41:34,484
Oh, is it discourteous of me

564
00:41:34,609 --> 00:41:37,070
to bring up something this personal
in front of your direct superior?

565
00:41:37,612 --> 00:41:39,197
Yes, it is discourteous.

566
00:41:42,283 --> 00:41:43,618
And what's so bad about that?

567
00:41:43,868 --> 00:41:45,453
The housing price in Seoul
has skyrocketed

568
00:41:45,537 --> 00:41:46,788
so it's nice and economical.

569
00:41:48,123 --> 00:41:49,124
You already knew?

570
00:41:50,375 --> 00:41:51,376
Of course.

571
00:41:52,669 --> 00:41:55,547
She's been to our place, too.

572
00:42:00,301 --> 00:42:01,302
Is that so?

573
00:42:05,056 --> 00:42:08,560
Since when did our company
begin to visit our employees at home?

574
00:42:18,486 --> 00:42:21,448
I'll have to ask to be excused.

575
00:42:21,990 --> 00:42:22,991
I was in the middle of work.

576
00:42:23,908 --> 00:42:24,951
Sit.

577
00:42:25,660 --> 00:42:27,495
We're sitting here at the same table

578
00:42:27,746 --> 00:42:29,664
so don't you think it's basic manners
to get up together?

579
00:42:33,001 --> 00:42:34,502
You have a point.

580
00:42:34,878 --> 00:42:36,046
I'll go with you, Mr. Noh.

581
00:42:36,463 --> 00:42:38,423
I almost forgot my manners
and sent you back alone.

582
00:42:39,174 --> 00:42:41,968
We were initially
in the middle of eating together.

583
00:42:42,510 --> 00:42:44,220
Please enjoy your lunch, you two.

584
00:42:44,345 --> 00:42:45,346
Let's go.

585
00:42:47,724 --> 00:42:48,808
Come on. Let's go.

586
00:43:02,489 --> 00:43:03,948
- Isn't it good?
- It is.

587
00:43:05,033 --> 00:43:09,037
We should never waste any food,
but I couldn't help it. What a shame.

588
00:43:10,205 --> 00:43:12,457
Anyway, this toast is really good.

589
00:43:12,540 --> 00:43:14,042
Is this your first time trying it?

590
00:43:14,125 --> 00:43:15,627
That place has been around forever.

591
00:43:16,211 --> 00:43:18,880
When I was new, the only fun I had
at work was getting this

592
00:43:19,005 --> 00:43:20,548
on my way to work
and eating it in the office.

593
00:43:21,549 --> 00:43:22,926
Did you get one
for the vice president?

594
00:43:23,843 --> 00:43:24,844
I don't know.

595
00:43:28,389 --> 00:43:30,141
He must be furious, right?

596
00:43:31,392 --> 00:43:33,311
How am I going to keep my career
in the future?

597
00:43:35,188 --> 00:43:37,398
Will you take responsibility
and protect your subordinate?

598
00:43:38,233 --> 00:43:39,692
So why did you act so cheekily?

599
00:43:40,902 --> 00:43:44,239
I mean, he was way too immature
for someone who's a vice president.

600
00:43:46,032 --> 00:43:49,661
Anyway, I can tell after today
that he's definitely still into you.

601
00:43:50,203 --> 00:43:52,413
Then what? Do you want to conduct
an additional investigation?

602
00:43:52,664 --> 00:43:54,999
No, you aren't into him,
so it doesn't matter.

603
00:43:56,501 --> 00:43:58,419
I guess some people remember

604
00:43:58,545 --> 00:44:01,089
their old relationship like the rose
from The Little Prince.

605
00:44:04,425 --> 00:44:06,845
- What do you mean by that?
- Don't you know it?

606
00:44:07,512 --> 00:44:09,013
The Little Prince comes to Earth

607
00:44:09,097 --> 00:44:11,349
and sees many roses
that are exactly the same-looking.

608
00:44:11,850 --> 00:44:13,017
Yet he returns to the planet

609
00:44:13,101 --> 00:44:14,936
where the rose
he spent time with lives.

610
00:44:16,688 --> 00:44:18,106
The Little Prince returns?

611
00:44:19,107 --> 00:44:20,483
Doesn't he live
with the fox on Earth?

612
00:44:20,567 --> 00:44:22,861
No, he returns to his planet.

613
00:44:23,444 --> 00:44:25,363
He wants to be responsible
for the rose he cultivated.

614
00:44:25,446 --> 00:44:26,614
No, he remains on Earth.

615
00:44:27,448 --> 00:44:30,285
No, he returns.
Do you want to make a bet?

616
00:44:31,452 --> 00:44:33,288
Bet? I'm in.

617
00:44:33,621 --> 00:44:35,874
We aren't betting on a wish,
but a penalty.

618
00:44:36,291 --> 00:44:37,292
Sure.

619
00:44:38,042 --> 00:44:40,336
"I'm returning to the star tonight."

620
00:44:40,461 --> 00:44:42,505
See? It means
he's returning to his planet.

621
00:44:44,424 --> 00:44:45,884
What? This is really sad.

622
00:44:46,926 --> 00:44:49,304
Why did I remember the story
as a happy ending? What is this?

623
00:44:49,721 --> 00:44:52,098
You must've interpreted this
as a happy ending back then.

624
00:44:53,558 --> 00:44:56,436
Why did he want to leave Earth
after the trouble of getting there?

625
00:45:00,315 --> 00:45:01,316
So I won, right?

626
00:45:02,650 --> 00:45:05,361
You must've been
an avid reader of children's tales.

627
00:45:07,238 --> 00:45:10,366
Admit to your defeat
and face your penalty.

628
00:45:11,868 --> 00:45:13,620
Admitted. What's the penalty?

629
00:45:16,789 --> 00:45:19,000
Now, what can I do here

630
00:45:19,542 --> 00:45:21,377
to turn this into a cruel fairy tale?

631
00:45:33,848 --> 00:45:34,974
What is it?

632
00:45:54,494 --> 00:45:57,038
Hey, Ms. Joo has finally gone cuckoo
in her head.

633
00:46:03,544 --> 00:46:04,963
Excuse me, Ms. Joo.

634
00:46:05,880 --> 00:46:08,258
Your hair...

635
00:46:11,886 --> 00:46:12,887
What about it?

636
00:46:15,056 --> 00:46:16,599
Isn't it adorable?

637
00:46:16,933 --> 00:46:19,018
I've been into these things lately.

638
00:46:26,067 --> 00:46:27,193
Get back to work.

639
00:46:43,042 --> 00:46:47,171
ART CLASS DIRECTOR

640
00:46:50,008 --> 00:46:51,217
Thank you.

641
00:46:51,426 --> 00:46:54,387
That's cute.
What in the world is that hairpin?

642
00:46:55,596 --> 00:46:58,016
Yes, right. I still had this on?

643
00:46:59,267 --> 00:47:00,393
How embarrassing.

644
00:47:00,852 --> 00:47:01,936
That's new.

645
00:47:02,395 --> 00:47:03,771
Is that the recent trend?

646
00:47:03,813 --> 00:47:06,774
No, it was a gift from someone

647
00:47:07,775 --> 00:47:09,277
as a penalty.

648
00:47:12,947 --> 00:47:13,948
Anyway.

649
00:47:15,116 --> 00:47:16,659
I don't have to come
as a model anymore?

650
00:47:17,452 --> 00:47:18,828
What's going on? Am I getting fired?

651
00:47:18,953 --> 00:47:21,122
I should've hired you officially
and paid you.

652
00:47:21,706 --> 00:47:25,293
The business has been slow,
so I've been shameless.

653
00:47:25,668 --> 00:47:28,254
Don't say that.
I did it because I wanted to.

654
00:47:29,380 --> 00:47:31,716
And you already know
that I needed this.

655
00:47:32,467 --> 00:47:33,593
Do you still need it?

656
00:47:36,971 --> 00:47:39,474
I've known you a long time, In-a.

657
00:47:40,391 --> 00:47:44,562
And lately, I've been thinking
that you might not need

658
00:47:44,645 --> 00:47:45,730
this time anymore.

659
00:47:46,939 --> 00:47:48,107
You've been laughing a lot.

660
00:47:50,068 --> 00:47:52,320
- Me?
- Yes, and you seem to be at peace.

661
00:47:54,030 --> 00:47:55,073
Tell me.

662
00:47:55,531 --> 00:47:56,824
You're seeing someone, right?

663
00:47:57,325 --> 00:47:58,826
Is it the one
who gave you that hairpin?

664
00:48:02,288 --> 00:48:04,624
No, this is way too...

665
00:48:05,291 --> 00:48:08,378
You're the flower of the Audit Team,
so why don't you put a flower on?

666
00:48:08,461 --> 00:48:09,837
All right.

667
00:48:11,839 --> 00:48:12,882
A pig.

668
00:48:13,424 --> 00:48:15,635
Next, a rabbit.

669
00:48:16,010 --> 00:48:17,136
Look to the side.

670
00:48:21,682 --> 00:48:25,061
- I can't.
- What do you mean? Why not?

671
00:48:26,479 --> 00:48:27,605
He's someone at work.

672
00:48:29,607 --> 00:48:32,777
In another country, there is
this phrase about dating at work.

673
00:48:33,903 --> 00:48:35,571
"Don't go number two where you eat."

674
00:48:37,698 --> 00:48:39,242
It means it's that insane.

675
00:48:39,325 --> 00:48:42,829
Why not? It's better than
holding it in and getting sick.

676
00:48:43,621 --> 00:48:46,290
I'm saying, who cares
if you do something crazy?

677
00:48:47,291 --> 00:48:51,170
Didn't you think this job was
also crazy before you did it?

678
00:48:51,504 --> 00:48:52,713
But after trying it

679
00:48:52,797 --> 00:48:54,924
it became the only escape
in your everyday life.

680
00:48:56,050 --> 00:48:57,718
Don't put a limit on yourself.

681
00:48:58,219 --> 00:49:01,931
Only when you break the limit
will you find new joy.

682
00:49:03,599 --> 00:49:06,477
Hey, Director.
You're good with words.

683
00:49:06,686 --> 00:49:07,937
You didn't know?

684
00:49:31,461 --> 00:49:35,047
RECREATIONAL ART CLASS
TONIGHT AT 9 P.M.

685
00:49:49,812 --> 00:49:51,564
Have I always been this pretty?

686
00:50:04,577 --> 00:50:05,620
You are pretty.

687
00:50:31,270 --> 00:50:33,981
AUDIT RESULT

688
00:50:39,237 --> 00:50:41,072
You didn't seem to eat much at lunch.

689
00:50:41,572 --> 00:50:42,698
You should have some.

690
00:50:44,492 --> 00:50:45,493
Okay.

691
00:50:45,993 --> 00:50:47,954
And you crossed the line earlier.

692
00:50:50,748 --> 00:50:52,375
You used me.

693
00:50:53,543 --> 00:50:54,669
I know that

694
00:50:55,670 --> 00:50:57,463
you like Ms. Joo In-a.

695
00:51:00,550 --> 00:51:02,510
I'm a very competent assistant

696
00:51:03,844 --> 00:51:05,680
and a woman who likes you.

697
00:51:08,349 --> 00:51:09,517
Ki-jun is

698
00:51:10,434 --> 00:51:11,936
a great guy.

699
00:51:13,563 --> 00:51:14,772
It was the first time I ran away

700
00:51:14,855 --> 00:51:16,524
feeling annoyed
that he found out about my situation

701
00:51:17,483 --> 00:51:20,027
and I didn't want to burden him.

702
00:51:20,653 --> 00:51:23,155
I didn't want to be
belittled before him.

703
00:51:31,664 --> 00:51:33,082
Why are you telling me this?

704
00:51:33,165 --> 00:51:35,835
I'm saying you have nothing on Ki-jun

705
00:51:37,878 --> 00:51:39,338
even for someone like you.

706
00:51:58,065 --> 00:52:01,152
HR REPORT
ON US EXPATRIATE

707
00:52:16,208 --> 00:52:17,918
- Enjoy.
- Thank you.

708
00:52:18,878 --> 00:52:20,504
- Two toasts, please.
- Sure.

709
00:52:20,588 --> 00:52:22,131
- Please make them delicious.
- Of course.

710
00:52:24,008 --> 00:52:26,260
- Enjoy.
- Thank you.

711
00:52:33,184 --> 00:52:34,602
What is this?

712
00:52:35,061 --> 00:52:36,437
What does he have to say now?

713
00:52:36,520 --> 00:52:38,439
HR HEAD AHN SEUNG-WOO, PERVERT

714
00:52:38,481 --> 00:52:40,149
MISSED CALLS FROM
HR HEAD AHN SEUNG-WOO, PERVERT

715
00:52:44,779 --> 00:52:48,157
Your call cannot be connected.
You will be redirected to voicemail.

716
00:52:48,282 --> 00:52:49,408
ASSISTANT MANAGER NOH KI-JUN

717
00:52:55,498 --> 00:52:57,291
Will you please pick up?

718
00:53:12,640 --> 00:53:13,641
Hey, Ki-jun!

719
00:53:13,849 --> 00:53:15,184
What's going on, man?

720
00:53:15,601 --> 00:53:17,311
You really got
on the vice president's good side.

721
00:53:17,812 --> 00:53:19,146
What are you talking about?

722
00:53:19,271 --> 00:53:20,981
Ms. Hong of HR told me everything.

723
00:53:21,065 --> 00:53:22,733
I heard you got assigned
as an expatriate to the US.

724
00:53:24,235 --> 00:53:25,236
What?

725
00:53:26,612 --> 00:53:27,697
I'm so jealous.

726
00:53:31,075 --> 00:53:33,703
Your call cannot be connected.
You will be redirected to voicemail.

727
00:53:38,040 --> 00:53:40,209
Goodness, Mr. Lee. Mr. Lee.

728
00:53:40,543 --> 00:53:42,002
Thank you for coming out
on your busy day.

729
00:53:42,712 --> 00:53:43,713
Yes.

730
00:53:50,052 --> 00:53:51,846
I can't have you keep calling me.

731
00:53:52,096 --> 00:53:54,014
Think of how desperate I am.

732
00:53:54,557 --> 00:53:56,600
I'm about to get divorced.

733
00:53:56,684 --> 00:53:58,060
My wife is now...

734
00:54:00,730 --> 00:54:03,274
She's banning me
from seeing my child, Do-yun.

735
00:54:05,443 --> 00:54:09,071
Can you help me
get a favorable arrangement

736
00:54:09,155 --> 00:54:11,365
or let me settle the case?

737
00:54:12,158 --> 00:54:14,034
Maybe the employees
can turn in petitions

738
00:54:14,076 --> 00:54:16,036
and say that I've worked hard

739
00:54:16,495 --> 00:54:18,706
and always had a great reputation.

740
00:54:19,874 --> 00:54:22,585
Well, even if I
personally made a move

741
00:54:23,377 --> 00:54:25,463
the Audit Team
is already set on this.

742
00:54:26,213 --> 00:54:30,843
I've also been
contacting Mr. Noh Ki-jun

743
00:54:31,552 --> 00:54:33,053
but he won't pick up his phone.

744
00:54:34,388 --> 00:54:37,183
Mr. Ahn, he's on a roll right now.

745
00:54:37,725 --> 00:54:40,060
He got a special promotion,
thanks to your incident

746
00:54:40,144 --> 00:54:41,729
and he even got a chance
to work in the US.

747
00:54:43,397 --> 00:54:44,440
You didn't know?

748
00:54:46,776 --> 00:54:50,070
Director Park, I hear your daughter
is getting married soon.

749
00:54:50,571 --> 00:54:51,655
Congratulations.

750
00:54:52,281 --> 00:54:54,200
Let me know when you have the date.

751
00:54:54,450 --> 00:54:55,910
I'd like to relay
my congratulatory message.

752
00:54:55,951 --> 00:54:58,579
Goodness, Director Park.
That wedding will be a big deal.

753
00:54:59,079 --> 00:55:03,375
Are you really willing to come
and share a message?

754
00:55:04,376 --> 00:55:06,587
Or do you think
a song will be better?

755
00:55:25,815 --> 00:55:28,275
Your call cannot be connected.
You will be redirected to voicemail.

756
00:55:28,484 --> 00:55:29,610
Why won't she pick up?

757
00:55:29,693 --> 00:55:30,778
JOO IN-A

758
00:55:34,907 --> 00:55:37,117
Your call cannot be connected.
You will be redirected to voicemail.

759
00:55:39,328 --> 00:55:41,705
Hey, have you seen Ms. Joo?

760
00:55:43,082 --> 00:55:44,250
Have you seen her?

761
00:55:44,708 --> 00:55:47,461
I didn't, but Seung-hee just told me

762
00:55:47,795 --> 00:55:50,714
that Ms. Joo suddenly showed up
and left with the vice president.

763
00:55:52,299 --> 00:55:53,342
Where did they go?

764
00:55:57,346 --> 00:55:58,472
What do you think you're doing?

765
00:55:58,556 --> 00:56:00,474
- What?
- About Mr. Noh Ki-jun!

766
00:56:00,599 --> 00:56:03,727
You did not say a word to him or me,
who has direct authority over him.

767
00:56:03,811 --> 00:56:05,229
How can you suddenly announce

768
00:56:05,312 --> 00:56:07,731
sending him away overnight
like he's some parcel?

769
00:56:07,940 --> 00:56:09,984
And you barged in there

770
00:56:10,401 --> 00:56:11,485
to nitpick over this?

771
00:56:12,444 --> 00:56:14,488
You dragged me out
of a meeting with the directors

772
00:56:14,572 --> 00:56:16,532
just to nitpick over
an assistant manager's position?

773
00:56:16,615 --> 00:56:18,200
It's not just his position.

774
00:56:18,284 --> 00:56:20,995
This is a matter of respect
for my duty and authority.

775
00:56:21,495 --> 00:56:23,539
You are not allowed
to appoint an employee like this

776
00:56:23,622 --> 00:56:25,165
if he has no reason
to be disciplined.

777
00:56:27,418 --> 00:56:28,878
This is unjust.

778
00:56:29,753 --> 00:56:30,963
And this calls for an audit.

779
00:56:31,922 --> 00:56:33,549
I've reviewed
the decision thoroughly.

780
00:56:33,924 --> 00:56:36,510
It's a loss to the business
for an employee with his performance

781
00:56:36,594 --> 00:56:38,929
and competence
to be cooped up doing PM duties.

782
00:56:41,682 --> 00:56:42,850
Is that really the reason

783
00:56:44,894 --> 00:56:46,687
and not because
of any personal feelings?

784
00:56:48,397 --> 00:56:49,690
It's the US expatriate position.

785
00:56:49,815 --> 00:56:52,443
That's a place
where every employee wants to go

786
00:56:52,526 --> 00:56:54,194
and it's a privilege
for an assistant manager.

787
00:56:54,737 --> 00:56:56,572
He'll also be promoted as a manager.

788
00:56:56,864 --> 00:56:58,532
Is this something
for you to be so angry over?

789
00:56:59,241 --> 00:57:02,077
In-a, don't you think
you're the one holding back

790
00:57:02,494 --> 00:57:04,955
a talented employee's career
because of your feelings?

791
00:57:06,540 --> 00:57:08,292
Can you honestly tell me

792
00:57:08,876 --> 00:57:11,211
that you are this furious
only due to official reasons?

793
00:57:16,717 --> 00:57:17,718
In-a.

794
00:57:18,719 --> 00:57:21,138
There are many decisions I can make.

795
00:57:22,222 --> 00:57:25,559
And among them, I believe I made
the most courteous one I could.

796
00:57:33,525 --> 00:57:36,236
Your call cannot be connected.
You will be redirected to voicemail.

797
00:57:37,237 --> 00:57:38,364
Mr. Noh Ki-jun.

798
00:57:42,409 --> 00:57:43,410
Mr. Ahn.

799
00:57:45,913 --> 00:57:48,582
I cannot have you visit
or contact me like this.

800
00:57:55,756 --> 00:57:57,007
Hey, you...

801
00:58:26,495 --> 00:58:28,497
EMERGENCY ROOM

802
00:59:13,167 --> 00:59:15,544
You can't drive like this.
Let me take you there.

803
00:59:33,854 --> 00:59:35,397
Is he still waiting
in the emergency room?

804
00:59:39,359 --> 00:59:41,862
No, it's okay. There's no need.
I'll call you back.

805
00:59:42,029 --> 00:59:43,447
I'll just get off here.

806
00:59:44,073 --> 00:59:45,365
It's still pretty far from here.

807
00:59:45,449 --> 00:59:48,327
Just past the intersection... In-a!

808
01:00:04,551 --> 01:00:05,761
It's heartbreaking.

809
01:00:10,641 --> 01:00:12,142
You must've been very lonely.

810
01:00:15,521 --> 01:00:17,106
You keep acting tough

811
01:00:19,900 --> 01:00:21,068
which is making it worse.

812
01:00:27,241 --> 01:00:28,408
Then will you

813
01:00:29,076 --> 01:00:30,494
answer my question...

814
01:00:38,377 --> 01:00:39,962
Why do you push me away?

815
01:00:53,934 --> 01:00:55,769
About your question, Mr. Noh...

816
01:00:57,396 --> 01:00:59,565
The real reason
why I keep pushing you away...

817
01:01:04,862 --> 01:01:05,946
I...

818
01:01:09,658 --> 01:01:10,784
I...

819
01:01:14,997 --> 01:01:17,916
FILING FOR LOVE

820
01:01:46,695 --> 01:01:49,114
Mr. Noh. I was scared. It was scary.

821
01:01:49,198 --> 01:01:52,534
I think you should come along
to the Jeju business trip, Ms. Joo.

822
01:01:52,743 --> 01:01:53,827
What are you doing?

823
01:01:53,952 --> 01:01:56,288
Are you sending an assistant manager
overseas because of your feelings?

824
01:01:56,496 --> 01:01:58,665
In-a, please just stay by my side.

825
01:01:59,082 --> 01:02:01,460
What's the real reason you sent me
to Audit Team Three?

826
01:02:02,085 --> 01:02:03,503
Was it to protect Jeon Jae-yeol?

827
01:02:03,754 --> 01:02:06,089
How do you expect me
to understand this whole situation?

828
01:02:06,173 --> 01:02:08,091
We need to talk right now!

829
01:02:08,550 --> 01:02:09,843
Oddly enough

830
01:02:09,927 --> 01:02:13,013
I have a habit of hiding the truth
when it matters most.

831
01:02:26,568 --> 01:02:28,570
Subtitles by Eunsook Youn
and Jennifer Lim
